          <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-container">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">What is a secondary education scheme?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>
                A government or private initiative that provides financial aid, infrastructure, scholarships, or support to improve secondary education.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">Who is eligible for secondary education schemes?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>
                Eligibility varies by scheme but may depend on factors such as income level, gender, caste/category (in some countries), disability status, and academic performance.
</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">Are secondary education schemes available for all students?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>
                Many schemes target economically weaker sections, girls, differently-abled students, or students from marginalized communities.
</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question">What financial assistance is provided under these schemes?</div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>
                Assistance may include scholarships, free books, uniforms, midday meals, hostel facilities, or fee waivers.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
